SIMPLE: shipshape
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shipshape
<hw>Ship"shape`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Arranged in a
manner befitting a ship; hence, trim; tidy; orderly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Even then she expressed her scorn for the lubbery executioner's
mode of tying a knot, and did it herself in a <qex>shipshape</qex>
orthodox manner.</q> <rj><qau>De Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Keep everything <qex>shipshape</qex>, for I must go</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shipshape</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Shipshape
<hw>Ship"shape`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In a shipshape
or seamanlike manner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shipworm</ent>⟦br⟧
